initialize uv ==> uv init
activating venv ==> .\.venv\Scripts\activate
adding library ==> uv add [library name]
to run python file ==> uv run [filename.py]



uv init — start a project (creates .venv, pyproject.toml, lockfile).
Example: uv init

uv add <pkg> — add a dependency (installs into the project venv).
Example: uv add requests

uv remove <pkg> — remove a dependency.
Example: uv remove requests

uv run <file> — run a script inside the project environment (no manual activate needed).
Example: uv run main.py

uv sync — make the environment match the lockfile (use when switching branches or anyone else changed deps).
Example: uv sync

uv lock — update/write the lockfile (use after adding/removing to capture exact versions).
Example: uv lock

uvx <tool> [args] — run a tool once in an ephemeral environment (great for one-off linters/formatters).
Example: uvx ruff check .
